headline: Week’s Best: ETFs Rake In Assets
summary: Investors poured a record amount of money into exchange-traded funds in 2025, according to State Street Investment Management.  Net inflows topped $1.5 trillion, eclipsing the previous record of $1.15 trillion set in 2024, and boosting the total amount of money invested in ETFs to $13.4 trillion.  Investors poured money into all types of exchange-traded funds last year with flows into bond, gold, and active equity ETFs all hitting records.

headline: Banks to report earnings next week: 3 things investors are watching
summary: Earnings season is close to kicking off for big banks, with companies JPMorgan Chase (JPM), Bank of America (BAC), Citigroup (C), Morgan Stanley (MS), Wells Fargo (WFC), and Goldman Sachs (GS) set to report their quarterly results throughout next week. Major US bank stocks notably ended 2025 at new record highs. Yahoo Finance senior bank reporter David Hollerith lists the three biggest themes that Wall Street investors will be watching from bank earnings. headline: What Catalysts Are Quietly Rewriting The Story For i3 Verticals (IIIV)
summary: i3 Verticals just went through a fresh valuation check, and while the model fair value estimate holds steady at US$34.17, the inputs behind that number tell a more nuanced story. With revenue growth assumptions largely intact and only a small tweak to the discount rate, most of the change in the price target narrative comes back to when certain projects are expected to show up in reported numbers, not a wholesale rethink of the business.
